WHereas by the Law made May 1669. respecting Book-debts; It is Declared, that all Book-Debts shall be cleared within three years, as is therein expressed, after which time no Book-Debt shall be pleadable in any Court: Upon a general complaint, that the said Law will prove to the real detriment of very many of our Inhabitants, and the utter undoing of some if a greater number of year 
